VALEXPB   PORTUGUESE   RULES (1.0)

   DP --> { "(QP) D: ^=! (^ PRED)='pro'" "to account for DPs without a NP or DP complement"
	    "|" (QP) Dbar
 	  | QP: ^=! (^ PRED)='pro' | D: ^=! (! PRON-TYPE)=c free (^ PRED)='pro'; VP: ! $ (^ ADJUNCT) (! SUBJ )= ^ }.

   Dbar --> { (D) {NumP | NP | PossP} | D: ^=! (! PRON-TYPE)=c pers (^ PRED)='pro'}. "TODO: only personal pronouns as D heads provide PRED feature to DP when used without complements"


